description: Commit messages — short, factual; no secrets in messages or diffs.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Commit style

- Use short, factual commit messages (imperative mood, one line when possible).
- Do not put API keys, tokens, passwords, internal URLs with credentials, or other secrets in commit messages or anywhere in the diff.
- If fixing a sensitive mistake, rotate the secret elsewhere; never describe the secret value in the message.
